{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"458a823a-5cca-4573-8e8a-cbfd59a8dace","content":"The template is **not quite ready** for NuGet publishing. Here's what's missing or should be improved:\n\n**Critical for NuGet:**\n1. **No `description`** — NuGet and `dotnet new` use this for discoverability. Add a top-level `\"description\"` field.\n2. **No `groupIdentity`** — Required for proper package update/versioning behavior (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n\n**Recommended:**\n3. **No `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for editor validation.\n4. **No `preferNameDirectory`** — Set to `true` so `dotnet new mywebapi -n Foo` creates a `Foo/` directory.\n5. **No `sourceName` for Framework** — The `Framework` symbol is defined but isn't wired to replace a `<TargetFramework>` value anywhere via `replaces`.\n\n**Also note:**\n6. The workspace has **no project files** (`.csproj`, content files, etc.) — the template has nothing to package yet.\n7. You'll need a **`.csproj` with `<PackageType>Template</PackageType>`** to produce a NuGet template package.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3ac3a069-bd26-4737-ae96-d3b840a41c8f","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"93C1:1D28CE:E043945:F678863:69F2A958"},"id":"df4884c2-03ff-4c68-a4e3-1ee39b0b1baf","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:59:13.170Z","parentId":"2130d97d-528c-4c66-8fa1-07cb8e928912"}
